p: Wherefore to be relieved from said unlawful detention and imprisonment your petitioner prays that a writ of Habeas Corpus to be directed to the said Lewis Byrd, may issue in this behalf, so that your petitioners may be forthwith brought before this court to do, submit to, and receive what the law may require.

Felip Perell and Prospro Deffillipps being duly sworn each for himself, deposes and says that he isthey are one of the petitioner named in the foregoing petition subscribed by him that they have heard the same read, and knows the contents thereof, and that the statements therein much are true as they verily beileves } Prospero Defilippes Filipp Perell
Subscribed and sworn to this 6th day of July 1886
